The SQL Server sa log in is a server-level principal

The sa login is a member of the sysadmin fixed server-level role. 

The sa login has all permissions on the server and cannot be limited.
The sa login cannot be dropped, but it can be disabled so that no one can use it.

By default, it is created when an instance is installed.

Beginning in SQL Server 2005 (9.x), the default database of sa is master. 

sa owns the databases 
   master,
   tempdb
   model (these ownerships cannot be changed)
and
   msdb
    
